# Amazon Clone

A simple Amazon homepage clone built using **HTML** and **CSS**. This project was created to practice web page structure, layouts, and styling by recreating the look and feel of the Amazon home page.

## Preview

![Amazon Clone Preview](amazon-clone-preview.png)

## Features

- Amazon-inspired navigation bar
- Search bar with category dropdown
- Hero banner section
- Product category cards
- Multi-column footer
- Clean and responsive layout
- Hover effects on navigation and product cards

## Technologies Used

- HTML5
- CSS3

## Folder Structure

```
amazon-clone/
│── index.html
│── style.css
│── amazon-clone-preview.png
│── README.md
```

## Getting Started

1. Clone this repository.

```bash
git clone https://github.com/amulya464/amazon-clone.git
```

2. Open the project folder.

3. Run `index.html` in your preferred web browser.

## Learning Outcomes

Working on this project helped me improve my understanding of:

- HTML page structure
- CSS Flexbox layouts
- Positioning and spacing
- Navigation bar design
- Responsive web design basics
- Organizing project files and assets

